-- CEZ Offers to Sell Coal-Power Plant to End EU Antitrust Probe
-- B y   A o i f e   W h i t e
-- 2012-07-10T09:45:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-10/cez-offers-to-sell-coal-power-plant-to-end-eu-antitrust-probe.html
CEZ AS (CEZ) , the Czech Republic’s largest
power producer, offered to sell a coal-power plant to end a
European Union antitrust probe over hindering rivals.  “CEZ offered to divest one of the following generation
assets in the Czech Republic: Pocerady, Chvaletice, Detmarovice
or Melnik III together with Tisova,” the European Commission
said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
